		{"id":"e6d7115c9d9e919b","type":"text","text":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vGUNqq3jVLg\n\ntranscript:\n0:00\n\n[Music]\n\n0:05\n\n5 seconds\n\nDon't move.\n\n0:08\n\n8 seconds\n\nPlease welcome the Emmy award-winning and so I'm nervous. I don't know why.\n\n0:11\n\n11 seconds\n\nCreators of South Park, Matt Stone and Trey Parker. You think I'm kidding, right?\n\n0:18\n\n18 seconds\n\nHey. Hey.\n\n0:24\n\n24 seconds\n\nOur whole South Park writers room, one whole wall is is one of these. And we've got it split up and into three acts. We\n\n0:32\n\n32 seconds\n\nhave different colored markers just like here, too. Look it. Yep. We have that.\n\n0:35\n\n35 seconds\n\nAnd I walk around with the markers like this. And we'll go, okay, we do a show about this. These are writers. Okay.\n\n0:39\n\n39 seconds\n\nOkay. Well, somewhere, okay, this would be a funny scene if we had this. Each individual scene has to work as a kind of funny sketch. You don't want one scene that's just like, well, what what\n\n0:46\n\n46 seconds\n\nwas the point of that scene? We found out this really simple rule that maybe you guys have all heard before, but it took us a long time to learn it. But we\n\n0:54\n\n54 seconds\n\ncan take these beats which are basically the beats of your outline. And if the words and then belong between those\n\n1:02\n\n1 minute, 2 seconds\n\nbeats, you're basically you got you got something pretty boring. What should happen between every beat that you've\n\n1:09\n\n1 minute, 9 seconds\n\nwritten down is either the word therefore or but right. So so what I'm saying is that you come up with an idea and it's like okay this happens, right?\n\n1:18\n\n1 minute, 18 seconds\n\nAnd then this happens. No, no, no.\n\n1:20\n\n1 minute, 20 seconds\n\nshould be this happens and therefore this happens but this happens therefore this happens and that as soon as we are\n\n1:28\n\n1 minute, 28 seconds\n\nable to and literally sometimes we'll we'll write it out to make sure we're doing it uh we'll we'll have our beats and we'll say okay this happened but\n\n1:36\n\n1 minute, 36 seconds\n\nthen this happens and that affects this and that does to that and that's why you get a show that feels like okay this to that to this to that but this here's the\n\n1:44\n\n1 minute, 44 seconds\n\ncomplication to that and there's so many scripts we read from new writers and and and things that we that I see movies.\n\n1:51\n\n1 minute, 51 seconds\n\nYeah. Yeah. You see movies that you're just watching. It's like this happened and then this happens and then this happens. That's when you're in a movie just going what the am I watching this movie for? Just like this happened\n\n2:00\n\n2 minutes\n\nand then this happened and this happened. That's not a movie, you know?\n\n2:02\n\n2 minutes, 2 seconds\n\nThat's not a story. Like Trey said, it's those those two but because therefore that gives you the causation between each beat and that makes that that's a story. Yeah.","x":-80,"y":-100,"width":468,"height":200},
		{"id":"8fbc543aebce1d73","type":"text","text":"maybe this is a way to explain to ai how to structure a node based plot","x":120,"y":-320,"width":250,"height":98},
		{"id":"b51d6dad7e23ab0d","type":"text","text":"i like the breakdown by uss palomar here:\n\n\n[https://www.reddit.com/r/writing/comments/14j8phe/something_i_wanted_to_know_about_and_then_but/](https://www.reddit.com/r/writing/comments/14j8phe/something_i_wanted_to_know_about_and_then_but/)\n\nThese aren't phrases that you would include in your manuscript (unless they _really really really_ create the effect you want in a transition) but are instead simplified ways of describing how to successive plot points relate to each other. The idea being (I think) that if you were casually summarizing the plot of your story, you'd use these sorts of phrases to explain how it all connects together.\n\n- \"And then\" would be two events happening in sequence without having any connection to each other. Bob eats a sandwich and then he sits down on his couch.\n\n- \"But then\" would be when there's some sort of turn and some event contrasts with or disrupts the previous one. Bob sits down on his couch but then there's a knock at the door.\n\n- \"And therefore\" would be when an event happens as a result of the one preceding it. The person knocking at the door is the Terminator, and therefore Bob has to run for his life.","x":-100,"y":200,"width":394,"height":460}
	],
